body:
It looks like the `MeasureText` method is computing the length of strings incorrectly. Here is an example of how the incorrect bounds are computed for text. I'm using the following snippet:

```
paint.Color = SKColors.Black;
paint.IsAntialias = true;
paint.TextEncoding = SKTextEncoding.Utf16;
paint.TextSize = 45;
SKRect bounds = new SKRect();
paint.MeasureText(text, ref bounds);
```

And the `bounds` rect is rendered like this, for several strings of differing lengths:
![text-width-bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/934815/15088086/6989e762-13bd-11e6-8cd5-74c819a4da31.png)

When I pad the string with spaces like so:

```
paint.Color = SKColors.Black;
paint.IsAntialias = true;
paint.TextEncoding = SKTextEncoding.Utf16;
paint.TextSize = 45;
SKRect bounds = new SKRect();
string padded = text;
for (int i = 0; i < text.Length; i++) padded += " ";
paint.MeasureText(padded, ref bounds);
```

The bounds are computed correctly:

![text-width-bug-padded](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/934815/15088139/da142452-13bd-11e6-9d74-05062ad499eb.png)
